sequenceDiagram
    actor Admin
    participant Browser
    participant Django
    participant Celery
    participant Polars
    participant SciPy
    participant DuckDB
    participant UMAP
    participant S3

    Admin->>Browser: Navigate to dataset detail page
    Browser->>Django: GET /training/<slug>/runs/
    Django-->>Browser: Render run list (empty or existing runs)

    Admin->>Browser: Fill start-run form (label, target, UMAP toggle)
    Browser->>Django: POST /training/<slug>/runs/start/
    Django->>Django: Validate form fields
    Django->>Django: Create ModelTrainingRun (status=PENDING)
    Django->>Celery: run_model_training_task.apply_async(run_id)
    Django-->>Browser: Redirect to /training/runs/<run_id>/

    Browser->>Django: GET /training/runs/<run_id>/
    Django-->>Browser: Render run detail page (status=PENDING)
    Browser->>Django: GET /training/runs/<run_id>/status/ [HTMX poll every 3s]
    Django-->>Browser: Status partial (PENDING)

    Note over Celery,S3: Async execution begins
    Celery->>Django: Update status → RUNNING
    Celery->>S3: Read dataset Parquet via s3fs
    S3-->>Celery: DataFrame bytes
    Celery->>Polars: Build DataFrame, normalise features
    Polars-->>Celery: Normalised train/val splits (80/20 stratified)

    loop Weight optimisation (L-BFGS-B / SLSQP)
        Celery->>SciPy: minimize(objective, x0, method=SLSQP, constraints, bounds)
        SciPy->>DuckDB: Compute target metric on val fold (Gini / KS / F1_Review)
        DuckDB-->>SciPy: Metric value
        SciPy-->>Celery: Candidate weights (converged)
    end

    Celery->>Celery: Threshold grid search (Cartesian product)
    Celery->>DuckDB: Evaluate each (t_approve, t_review) pair on val fold
    DuckDB-->>Celery: Best threshold pair

    opt umap_enabled == True
        Celery->>UMAP: Fit 2-D embedding on 4-feature train fold
        UMAP-->>Celery: (x, y) coordinates per sample
        Celery->>S3: Write umap.parquet
    end

    Celery->>S3: Write weights.json
    Celery->>S3: Write thresholds.json
    Celery->>S3: Write val_metrics.json
    Celery->>S3: Write score_distributions.parquet
    Celery->>Django: Update ModelTrainingRun (status=COMPLETED, metrics, artefacts_s3_path)

    Browser->>Django: GET /training/runs/<run_id>/status/ [HTMX poll]
    Django-->>Browser: Status partial (COMPLETED — stops polling)
    Browser->>Django: GET /training/runs/<run_id>/
    Django-->>Browser: Run detail with metrics, links to backtest & promotion
